Make a list of median along a sliding window for all sites, nonsyn sites and syn sites

#This is for all sites
ProandRTdata<-OverviewDF

#For NonSynSites
ProandRTdataNonSyn<-OverviewDFNonSyn

#For SynSites
ProandRTdataSyn<-OverviewDFSyn

#making the sliding windows
library(zoo)
## 
## Attaching package: 'zoo'
## The following objects are masked from 'package:base':
## 
##     as.Date, as.Date.numeric
ListMeans<- zoo(ProandRTdata$colMeansTs)
ListMedianWindow<- c(rollapply(ListMeans, width = 40, by = 1, FUN = median, align = "left"))


#for non-sy sites
ListMeansNonSyn<- zoo(ProandRTdataNonSyn$colMeansTs)
ListMedianWindowNonSyn<- c(rollapply(ListMeansNonSyn, width = 40, by = 1, FUN = median, align = "left"))
ListVarWindowNonSyn<-c(rollapply(ListMedianWindowNonSyn, width = 2, by = 1, FUN = var, align = "left"))

#for Syn Sites
ListMeansSyn<- zoo(ProandRTdataSyn$colMeansTs)
ListMedianWindowSyn<- c(rollapply(ListMeansSyn, width = 40, by = 1, FUN = median, align = "left"))
ListVarWindowSyn<-c(rollapply(ListMedianWindowSyn, width = 2, by = 1, FUN = var, align = "left"))



#Plot mean values of all sites and median of sliding window
plot(ProandRTdata$num[order(ProandRTdata$num)],ProandRTdata$colMeansTs[order(ProandRTdata$num)]+0.0001,col=ProandRTdata$color[order(ProandRTdata$num)],pch=16,log="y",type="b")

points(1:945, ListMedianWindow, col="green",pch = 8, cex=3)

Randomization for All Sites

#randomization of means per sites

consensusB<-c(consensusB)
consenBcolMeans<-rbind(colMeansTs, consensusB)
Asites<-which(consensusB=="a")
Csites<-which(consensusB=="c")
Gsites<-which(consensusB=="g")
Tsites<-which(consensusB=="t")

#switch all sites
ListOfVarsAllSites<-c()
for (j in 1:1000){
  colMeansRandom<-ProandRTdata$colMeansTs
  colMeansRandom[Asites]<-colMeansRandom[sample(Asites)]
  colMeansRandom[Csites]<-colMeansRandom[sample(Csites)]
  colMeansRandom[Gsites]<-colMeansRandom[sample(Gsites)]
  colMeansRandom[Tsites]<-colMeansRandom[sample(Tsites)]

ListMedianRandomWindow<-c(rollapply(colMeansRandom, width = 40, by = 1, FUN = median, na.rm = TRUE, align = "left"))
ListOfVarsAllSites<-c(ListOfVarsAllSites,var(ListMedianRandomWindow))  
}


hist(ListOfVarsAllSites,xlim=c(min(c(ListOfVarsAllSites,var(ListMedianWindow))),max(c(ListOfVarsAllSites,var(ListMedianWindow)))))
abline(v=var(ListMedianWindow),col=2)

#rank and calculate p-value

plot(ListMedianWindow,log="y",ylim=c(0.001,0.1))
points(ListMedianRandomWindow,col=5,t="l")
